            "summary": "The professor opens Chapter 3 by revisiting the definition of a process as a program in execution, emphasizing that a process is an active entity while a program is a passive one. The distinction is reinforced by explaining that multiple running instances of the same application each constitute separate processes. The OS treats these instances independently because they may behave differently at runtime, even though they originate from the same binary. This foundational framing sets up why the OS must track and manage each process individually.",
