            "title": "Writing the MergeSort Recursive Pseudocode with Base Case",
            "start_sec": 1082.81,
            "summary": "The professor writes the complete top-level MergeSort pseudocode, computing midpoint Q, making the two recursive calls on [P..Q] and [Q+1..R], and calling Merge. A critical missing piece\u2014the base case\u2014is surfaced through student interaction: when P equals R the subarray has size 1 and is already sorted, so the function returns immediately without recursing. The professor also addresses whether size-zero subarrays can occur in MergeSort (they cannot, unlike QuickSort), ruling out the need for a P > R guard. This completes the main routine and sets up the remaining task of implementing the Merge subroutine.",
