            "id": "array_exhaustion_problem",
            "label": "Array Exhaustion Problem in Merge",
            "definition": "During merging, one temporary array may run out of elements before the other, creating a boundary-handling problem. The lecture points out that if this case is ignored, the algorithm may read beyond allocated memory and compare valid values against garbage.",
            "intuition": "At some point one side finishes, so the code must avoid reading past its end.",
