            "id": "boundary_check_method",
            "label": "Boundary-Check Method",
            "definition": "A second strategy for handling exhaustion is to add explicit conditions checking whether i or j has reached the end of its temporary array. If one side is exhausted, the remaining elements from the other side can be copied directly.",
