            "label": "Break-and-Copy-Remainder Method",
            "definition": "A third strategy is to break out of the main comparison loop once one temporary array is exhausted, then copy the remainder of the other array in one pass. The lecture presents this as another correct way to complete the merge after the main comparisons are done.",
