            "id": "bfs_non_uniqueness",
            "label": "Non-Unique BFS Tree",
            "definition": "The non-uniqueness of a BFS tree means different valid BFS runs can produce different parent choices and traversal orders, depending on neighbor ordering, while preserving the same distance levels. The lecture highlights this distinction explicitly.",
