            "id": "time_complexity_ve",
            "label": "BFS Time Complexity O(V + E)",
            "definition": "The running time of BFS with an adjacency-list representation is O(V + E), where V is the number of vertices and E is the number of edges. The lecture justifies this by aggregate counting: each vertex is initialized and processed a constant number of times, and each adjacency-list entry is examined at most once overall.",
            "intuition": "BFS is linear in the size of the graph representation.",
            "importance": 0.93,
            "depth": "deep_dive",
