            "solution": "One correct DFA is:\n\nStates:\n- `q0` = start state, before reading first symbol\n- `qA` = accept state, meaning the string started with `1`\n- `qT` = trap state, meaning the string started with `0`\n\nAlphabet:\n- `\u03a3 = {0,1}`\n\nTransitions:\n- From `q0`:\n  - on `1` \u2192 `qA`\n  - on `0` \u2192 `qT`\n- From `qA`:\n  - on `0` \u2192 `qA`\n  - on `1` \u2192 `qA`\n- From `qT`:\n  - on `0` \u2192 `qT`\n  - on `1` \u2192 `qT`\n\nAccept states:\n- `{qA}`\n\nWhy it works:\n- If the first symbol is `1`, the machine moves to `qA` and stays there, so the string is accepted.\n- If the first symbol is `0`, the machine moves to `qT` and stays rejected forever.\n- Every state has a transition on both `0` and `1`, so it is a valid DFA.",
