            "solution": "One decider for L works as follows:\n\n1. Scan the tape to verify there is exactly one #. If not, reject.\n2. Return to the left end.\n3. Find the first unmarked symbol before #.\n   - If there is none, go to step 7.\n4. If that symbol is a, replace it with a marker such as X. If it is b, replace it with a marker such as Y.\n5. Move right past # until you find the first unmarked symbol on the right side.\n   - If there is no unmarked symbol there, reject because the right side is too short.\n   - If the remembered left symbol was a, this symbol must be a; otherwise reject.\n   - If the remembered left symbol was b, this symbol must be b; otherwise reject.\n   - Mark the matched symbol on the right as well.\n6. Move back to the left side and repeat from step 3.\n7. Once no unmarked symbol remains before #, scan the right side.\n   - If any unmarked a or b remains after #, reject because the right side is too long.\n   - Otherwise accept.\n\nWhy this halts: each repetition marks at least one previously unmarked symbol on the left and one on the right, so progress is made. Eventually either a mismatch is found and the machine rejects, or all symbols are matched and the machine accepts.",
