            "id": "non_termination",
            "label": "Non-Termination",
            "definition": "Unlike finite automata and pushdown automata, a Turing machine computation is not guaranteed to halt on every input. The lecture emphasizes that algorithms may fail to terminate because of infinite loops or recursion without a base case.",
