            "title": "Scanning in Compilers: Role of Finite Automata and Regular Expressions",
            "start_sec": 7.94,
            "summary": "The professor situates scanning as the first phase of compilation, building on a prior overview of compiler components. Scanning is defined as the process of recognizing tokens from source text, and finite automata plus regular expressions are identified as the tools that make this possible. The lecture is framed as a review of CSC 135 theory-of-computation concepts, with emphasis on the ideas most relevant to building a scanner. Students are told the session will culminate in explaining how these theoretical tools connect to real scanner construction.",
