            "front": "Trace how you would recognize the language of all strings of odd length over an alphabet \u03a3.",
            "back": "Use a regular expression like \u03a3(\u03a3\u03a3)* or (\u03a3\u03a3)*\u03a3. The single \u03a3 contributes one symbol, and each \u03a3\u03a3 pair adds two more, giving lengths 1, 3, 5, 7, ... .",
