        "definition": "The knapsack recurrence computes the best value for state (i, j) by choosing the better of two cases: not taking item i, or taking item i if it fits and adding its value to the best solution for the remaining capacity. This recurrence formalizes the take-versus-skip decision central to 0-1 knapsack DP.",
        "intuition": "At each item, compare skipping it against taking it.",
        "global_importance": 1.0,
